---
import Default from "../layouts/Default.astro";
---

<Default
  title="tinygpt — a transformer playground, in the browser and on your Mac"
  description="Train, fine-tune, distil, interpret. Every modern architectural idea has a clean one-file implementation here — runnable in your browser via WebGPU or on your Mac via MLX."
>
  <main class="landing">
    <header class="hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">tinygpt</p>
      <h1>A transformer playground, in the browser <span class="and">and</span> on your Mac.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Train an LLM from scratch in your browser via WebGPU, or run the
        same architecture natively on Apple Silicon via MLX. Every
        modern technique &mdash; <em>MoE</em>, <em>MTP</em>,
        <em>ALiBi</em>, <em>differential attention</em>,
        <em>distillation</em>, <em>DoRA</em>, <em>StreamingLLM</em>
        &mdash; ships as a single clean Swift or TypeScript file, with
        a paper link next to it.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="cta primary" href="/playground">
          <span class="cta-label">Train in your browser</span>
          <span class="cta-sub">WebGPU · works on M-series Macs + modern Chrome</span>
        </a>
        <a class="cta secondary" href="https://github.com/sarthakagrawal927/tinygpt/tree/main/native-mac" rel="noopener">
          <span class="cta-label">Run on your Mac</span>
          <span class="cta-sub">CLI + SwiftUI app · MLX-Swift, Apple-native</span>
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="hero-fineprint">
        Open source under MIT. Source: <a href="https://github.com/sarthakagrawal927/tinygpt" rel="noopener">github/tinygpt</a>.
        Single-machine roadmap: <a href="/roadmap">7 parts</a>, 10 shipping phases.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="card-section" id="architecture">
      <h2>Architecture menu</h2>
      <p class="section-blurb">
        Every block is one file. The CLI accepts each as an opt-in flag
        (<code>--moe-experts</code>, <code>--mtp-horizons</code>,
        <code>--diff-attn</code>, <code>--yoco</code>, &hellip;) so
        configurations compose &mdash; you can train a Huge model with
        MoE <em>and</em> MTP <em>and</em> differential attention
        simultaneously, validated in a single shipped run.
      </p>

      <div class="capability-grid">
        <article class="capability">
          <header>
            <h3>Attention variants</h3>
            <p>Plug-in alternatives to standard causal MHA.</p>
          </header>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>RoPE + GQA</strong> &mdash; HF-Llama-compatible baseline (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2104.09864" rel="noopener">RoPE</a>, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.13245" rel="noopener">GQA</a>)</li>
            <li><strong>ALiBi</strong> &mdash; linear position bias (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2108.12409" rel="noopener">Press et al., 2021</a>)</li>
            <li><strong>Sliding window</strong> &mdash; Mistral / GPT-OSS recipe</li>
            <li><strong>Differential attention</strong> &mdash; subtract two softmaxes (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.05258" rel="noopener">Ye et al., 2024</a>)</li>
            <li><strong>YOCO</strong> &mdash; cross-layer KV sharing (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2405.05254" rel="noopener">Lin et al., 2024</a>)</li>
            <li><strong>StreamingLLM</strong> &mdash; attention sink for infinite context (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2309.17453" rel="noopener">Xiao et al., 2024</a>)</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="capability">
          <header>
            <h3>Sparsity &amp; scale</h3>
            <p>Capacity per byte of memory.</p>
          </header>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>MoE</strong> &mdash; router + experts + load-balance loss (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2101.03961" rel="noopener">Switch Transformer</a>, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2401.04088" rel="noopener">Mixtral</a>)</li>
            <li><strong>Multi-Token Prediction</strong> &mdash; H output heads (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2404.19737" rel="noopener">Gloeckle et al., 2024</a>, used by DeepSeek-V3)</li>
            <li><strong>Mixture of Depths</strong> &mdash; per-token sigmoid gate per block (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2404.02258" rel="noopener">Raposo et al., 2024</a>)</li>
            <li>See <a href="/docs/moe">docs/moe.md</a> for save/load + the scatter_add upstream gap that limits sparse compute today.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="capability">
          <header>
            <h3>Training</h3>
            <p>Pre-train, instruction-tune, prefer.</p>
          </header>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Pre-train</strong> on raw text (byte-level or BPE via any HuggingFace tokenizer)</li>
            <li><strong>SFT</strong> with response-only loss masking (ChatML / Alpaca / Llama / plain)</li>
            <li><strong>DPO</strong> + <strong>SimPO</strong> / <strong>ORPO</strong> / <strong>KTO</strong> &mdash; preference variants in one trainer (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.18290" rel="noopener">DPO</a>, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2405.14734" rel="noopener">SimPO</a>, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2403.07691" rel="noopener">ORPO</a>, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2402.01306" rel="noopener">KTO</a>)</li>
            <li><strong>Distillation</strong> &mdash; KL + NLL mix, temperature, alpha (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1503.02531" rel="noopener">Hinton et al., 2015</a>)</li>
            <li><strong>Evolution Strategies</strong> &mdash; gradient-free, antithetic sampling (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1703.03864" rel="noopener">Salimans et al., 2017</a>)</li>
            <li><strong>LoRA</strong> + <strong>LoRA+</strong> + <strong>DoRA</strong> + NEFTune + grad-clip + cosine LR</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="capability">
          <header>
            <h3>Inference</h3>
            <p>Fast, small, long-context.</p>
          </header>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>KV cache</strong> with optional fp16/bf16 quantisation</li>
            <li><strong>Prefix caching</strong> &mdash; save prompt KV state to disk, skip prefill on reload</li>
            <li><strong>Speculative decoding</strong> (greedy) &mdash; draft + verify (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2211.17192" rel="noopener">Leviathan et al., 2023</a>)</li>
            <li><strong>StreamingLLM</strong> sink + window for unbounded context</li>
            <li><strong>int4 / int8</strong> weight quantisation via MLX, plus <strong>HQQ</strong> sub-quadratic solver (<a href="https://mobiusml.github.io/hqq_blog/" rel="noopener">Badri &amp; Shaji, 2023</a>) and <strong>AWQ</strong> reader (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2306.00978" rel="noopener">Lin et al., 2023</a>)</li>
            <li><strong>LASER</strong> selective rank reduction (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2312.13558" rel="noopener">Sharma et al., 2024</a>)</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="capability">
          <header>
            <h3>Interpretability</h3>
            <p>What is this thing actually doing?</p>
          </header>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Logit lens</strong> &mdash; per-layer next-token predictions (<a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/AcKRB8wDpdaN6v6ru/interpreting-gpt-the-logit-lens" rel="noopener">Nostalgebraist, 2020</a>)</li>
            <li><strong>Tuned lens</strong> &mdash; trained per-layer probes (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2303.08112" rel="noopener">Belrose et al., 2023</a>)</li>
            <li><strong>Attention heatmap</strong> &mdash; per-head weights, "watch the model think"</li>
            <li><strong>Per-layer ablation</strong> &mdash; zero out attn / mlp / whole block, observe</li>
            <li><strong>Activation patching</strong> &mdash; intervene on residual stream at (layer, position) (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2202.05262" rel="noopener">Meng et al., 2022</a>)</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="capability">
          <header>
            <h3>Data</h3>
            <p>Where the bytes come from.</p>
          </header>
          <ul>
            <li>Any HuggingFace dataset via streaming importer (<code>python_ref/fetch_hf_corpus.py</code>)</li>
            <li>Wikipedia article fetcher (browser-side, in the playground)</li>
            <li>Project Gutenberg corpus (19 books, ~34 MB &mdash; bundled)</li>
            <li><strong>Magpie</strong> synthetic SFT data &mdash; bootstrap from a chat-tuned base (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2406.08464" rel="noopener">Xu et al., 2024</a>)</li>
            <li>Persistent tokenized corpus cache (skips re-tokenisation across runs)</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="card-section" id="run-it">
      <h2>Run it</h2>
      <div class="run-it-grid">
        <article class="platform-card">
          <header>
            <h3>In your browser</h3>
            <p class="platform-tag">WebGPU · in-tab training · works on M-series Macs and modern Chrome</p>
          </header>
          <p>
            The browser playground builds a transformer in WebAssembly + WebGPU, trains
            it in a Web Worker so the UI never freezes, and lets you watch the loss curve
            live as the model picks up structure. Every interpretability surface above is
            wired into a single Sample card &mdash; benchmark, logit lens, ablation, all
            under one collapsible &ldquo;Inspect &amp; evaluate&rdquo; panel.
          </p>
          <p class="card-cta">
            <a href="/playground" class="inline-cta">Open the playground &rarr;</a>
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="platform-card">
          <header>
            <h3>On your Mac</h3>
            <p class="platform-tag">MLX-Swift · CLI + SwiftUI app · trains models the browser can&rsquo;t fit</p>
          </header>
          <p>
            The Mac binary uses MLX-Swift to train preset sizes up to Titan (1.3B
            parameters) on Apple Silicon&rsquo;s unified memory. The same architecture
            ships as a CLI (<code>tinygpt train</code>, <code>sft</code>, <code>dpo</code>,
            <code>distill</code>, <code>es</code>, <code>laser</code>, <code>hqq</code>,
            <code>tuned-lens</code>, <code>magpie</code>) and a SwiftUI app for
            point-and-click fine-tuning.
          </p>
          <p class="card-cta">
            <a href="https://github.com/sarthakagrawal927/tinygpt/tree/main/native-mac" rel="noopener" class="inline-cta">Build it from source &rarr;</a>
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="card-section" id="learn">
      <h2>Learn how it&rsquo;s built</h2>
      <p class="section-blurb">
        Phase-by-phase guides cover every shipped feature with paper
        references and reproducible commands.
      </p>
      <div class="doc-grid">
        <a class="doc-link" href="/docs/model_guide">The model from scratch <span>byte-level GPT, attention, MLP, LayerNorm &mdash; explained in code</span></a>
        <a class="doc-link" href="/docs/training_phases">Three phases of training <span>pretrain &rarr; SFT &rarr; DPO, with commands you can paste</span></a>
        <a class="doc-link" href="/docs/distillation">Knowledge distillation <span>teacher &rarr; student with the KL+NLL mix loss</span></a>
        <a class="doc-link" href="/docs/moe">Mixture-of-Experts <span>router, experts, load balance, save/load &mdash; and the upstream gap that blocks real sparse compute</span></a>
        <a class="doc-link" href="/docs/mtp">Multi-Token Prediction <span>training-only extra heads &mdash; checkpoints stay drop-in compatible</span></a>
        <a class="doc-link" href="/docs/evolution_strategies">Evolution Strategies <span>gradient-free training (Salimans et al., 2017)</span></a>
        <a class="doc-link" href="/docs/interpretability">Interpretability tools <span>logit lens, tuned lens, ablation, activation patching</span></a>
        <a class="doc-link" href="/docs/memory_tradeoffs">Memory tradeoffs <span>bf16, gradient accumulation, sliding window &mdash; what fits in 48 GB</span></a>
        <a class="doc-link" href="/docs/validation_report">Validation report <span>end-to-end runs with actual loss numbers and the bugs the validation caught</span></a>
        <a class="doc-link" href="/docs/phase_9_10_status">Phase 9 + 10 status <span>quantisation + architecture menu: what shipped, what&rsquo;s queued</span></a>
        <a class="doc-link" href="/docs/single_machine_roadmap">Single-machine roadmap <span>every technique that runs on one Mac, ROI-ranked</span></a>
        <a class="doc-link" href="/docs/leaderboard">Leaderboard guide <span>how the three launch benchmarks are scored + how to submit</span></a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="card-section" id="numbers">
      <h2>Numbers</h2>
      <p class="section-blurb">
        Concrete loss curves and benchmark scores live on the
        <a href="/leaderboard">leaderboard</a>. The
        <a href="/docs/validation_report">validation report</a> walks
        through an end-to-end pipeline that exercises every shipped
        feature with real corpus + real numbers.
      </p>
      <ul class="numbers-list">
        <li><span class="n-label">Phase 1 validation, Huge + DiffAttn + MoD on FineWeb-Edu:</span> <span class="n-value">loss 11.22 &rarr; 6.46 over 500 steps</span> <span class="n-note">(val 6.49, no overfit, no NaN; commit <code>6cbe693</code>)</span></li>
        <li><span class="n-label">MoE distillation:</span> <span class="n-value">tiny MoE student (4 experts &times; top-2)</span> <span class="n-note">distilled from the above teacher; loss 1.93 &rarr; 0.21 in 30 steps; full MoE structure round-tripped through save/load/sample</span></li>
        <li><span class="n-label">Tuned-lens probes:</span> <span class="n-value">4 layer probes</span> <span class="n-note">trained on a frozen base, sidecar file format verified</span></li>
        <li><span class="n-label">Two real bugs caught</span> by the autonomous validation loop (tuned-lens crash, Astro build break) &mdash; commits <code>a64de95</code> + <code>9877bb7</code>. Static analysis passed; runtime didn&rsquo;t.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <footer class="landing-footer">
      <p>
        <a href="/leaderboard">Leaderboard</a> &middot;
        <a href="/devlog">Devlog</a> &middot;
        <a href="/roadmap">Roadmap</a> &middot;
        <a href="/docs">Docs</a> &middot;
        <a href="https://github.com/sarthakagrawal927/tinygpt" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
      </p>
      <p class="footnote">
        Built as a study of "what does every modern LLM idea actually
        look like as one file?". MIT licensed. The browser playground
        runs everything client-side &mdash; no server, no inference API.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </main>
</Default>

<style is:global>
  :root {
    --bg: #08090a;
    --bg-card: #0e1014;
    --bg-card-hover: #11141a;
    --fg: #e8eaed;
    --fg-soft: #c0c4cc;
    --muted: #8a8f99;
    --faint: #5a5e66;
    --line: #1c1f26;
    --line-strong: #262a33;
    --accent: #7aa7ff;
    --accent-dim: rgba(122, 167, 255, 0.35);
    --warm: #ffb072;
    --font-sans: "Geist", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
    --font-mono: "Geist Mono", ui-monospace, "SFMono-Regular", Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  html, body {
    margin: 0; padding: 0;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--fg);
    font: 400 15px/1.6 var(--font-sans);
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }
  code {
    font: 400 12.5px/1.4 var(--font-mono);
    background: var(--line);
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    color: var(--fg-soft);
  }
  a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: var(--accent-dim); text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  a:hover { text-decoration-color: var(--accent); }

  .landing {
    max-width: 940px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 64px 24px 96px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .landing { padding: 36px 18px 60px; }
  }

  /* Hero ----------------------------------------------------------- */
  .hero { margin-bottom: 80px; }
  .hero .eyebrow {
    font: 500 13px/1 var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: lowercase;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .hero h1 {
    font: 600 44px/1.18 var(--font-sans);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--fg);
    margin: 0 0 22px;
  }
  .hero h1 .and {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .hero h1 { font-size: 32px; }
  }
  .hero .lede {
    font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--fg-soft);
    margin: 0 0 32px;
    max-width: 740px;
  }
  .hero .lede em {
    font-style: normal;
    color: var(--fg);
    background: linear-gradient(transparent 70%, var(--accent-dim) 70%);
    padding: 0 1px;
  }
  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 22px;
  }
  .cta {
    display: inline-flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
    padding: 16px 22px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    transition: transform 120ms, background 120ms, border-color 120ms;
  }
  .cta:hover { transform: translateY(-1px); }
  .cta-label {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .cta-sub {
    font-size: 11.5px;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 400;
  }
  .cta.primary {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #06080c;
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
  }
  .cta.primary .cta-sub { color: rgba(6, 8, 12, 0.7); }
  .cta.primary:hover { background: #95b8ff; border-color: #95b8ff; }
  .cta.secondary {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--fg);
    border: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
  }
  .cta.secondary:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--bg-card-hover);
  }
  .hero-fineprint {
    font-size: 12.5px;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Section scaffold ----------------------------------------------- */
  .card-section {
    margin-bottom: 80px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding-top: 56px;
  }
  .card-section h2 {
    font: 500 24px/1.2 var(--font-sans);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    color: var(--fg);
  }
  .section-blurb {
    font-size: 14.5px;
    color: var(--fg-soft);
    margin: 0 0 32px;
    max-width: 720px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* Architecture menu ---------------------------------------------- */
  .capability-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .capability {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 22px 22px 18px;
    transition: border-color 120ms;
  }
  .capability:hover { border-color: var(--line-strong); }
  .capability header { margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .capability h3 {
    font: 500 15px/1.3 var(--font-sans);
    margin: 0 0 4px;
    color: var(--fg);
  }
  .capability header p {
    font-size: 12.5px;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .capability ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0; padding: 0;
  }
  .capability li {
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--fg-soft);
    padding: 5px 0;
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--line);
  }
  .capability li:first-child { border-top: none; }
  .capability li strong { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 500; }

  /* Run it --------------------------------------------------------- */
  .run-it-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .run-it-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .platform-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 24px 24px 22px;
  }
  .platform-card h3 {
    font: 500 18px/1.2 var(--font-sans);
    margin: 0 0 4px;
    color: var(--fg);
  }
  .platform-tag {
    font: 400 12px/1.4 var(--font-sans);
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .platform-card p {
    font-size: 13.5px;
    color: var(--fg-soft);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .card-cta { margin: 18px 0 0; }
  .inline-cta {
    font-weight: 500;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .inline-cta:hover { text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: var(--accent); }

  /* Doc grid ------------------------------------------------------- */
  .doc-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--line);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .doc-link {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
    padding: 16px 18px;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--fg);
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: background 100ms;
  }
  .doc-link:hover { background: var(--bg-card-hover); }
  .doc-link span {
    font-size: 12.5px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Numbers -------------------------------------------------------- */
  .numbers-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0; padding: 0;
  }
  .numbers-list li {
    padding: 14px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--fg-soft);
  }
  .numbers-list li:first-child { border-top: none; }
  .n-label { color: var(--muted); }
  .n-value { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 500; }
  .n-note { color: var(--muted); font-size: 12.5px; display: block; margin-top: 2px; }

  /* Footer --------------------------------------------------------- */
  .landing-footer {
    margin-top: 80px;
    padding-top: 28px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .landing-footer p { margin: 0 0 12px; font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--muted); }
  .landing-footer .footnote { font-size: 12px; color: var(--faint); max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.6; }
</style>
